                "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                "image": {
                    "type": "image",
                    "name": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                },
                "html": "Mudwretches are rarely encountered alone. They inhabit swampy patches in small groups, often gathering near the ruins of sites that once held great significance. Mudwretches can remain dormant for centuries, always eager to lurch up to attack passersby. They're usually more interested in defending territory than killing intruders, and they won't pursue victims for long if they flee."
            }
